	<clause id="ccds1970tai" obligation="normative"><title>Definition of TAI (PV, 38, 110-111 and <em>Metrologia</em>, 1971, 7, 43)</title><note id="_4ae703b4-d735-4d23-a1e0-4bf6fbf55325"><p id="_7126a3fb-6ea2-4f8e-9fa2-0e168143e80b">This definition was further amplified by the International Astronomical Union in 1991, Resolution A4:</p>
	<p id="_d6da11a7-a521-4efd-80c4-7bee5b93cb75">“TAI is a realized time scale whose ideal form, neglecting a constant offset of 32.184 s, is Terrestrial Time (TT), itself related to the time coordinate of the geocentric reference frame, Geocentric Coordinate Time (TCG), by a constant rate.”</p>
