	<clause id="cipm2001" obligation="normative">
	<title>CIPM, 2001</title>
	<clause id="cipm-si-units" obligation="normative"><title>“SI units” and “units of the SI” (PV, 69, 120) <index><primary>prefixes</primary></index></title><p id="_5fff72b5-c239-4903-8f63-21dcf7035a6b">The CIPM approved in 2001 the following proposal of the CCU regarding “SI units” and “units of the SI”:</p>
	<quote id="_ea7cc80e-1b77-41f3-adfd-11de4c22df51"><p id="_8f6756e2-3d0b-4f67-ad21-5907a2bcd686">“We suggest that “SI units” and “units of the SI” should be regarded as names that include both the base units<index><primary>base unit(s)</primary></index> and the coherent derived units<index><primary>coherent derived units</primary></index>, and also all units obtained by combining these with the recommended multiple and sub-multiple prefixes.</p>
	<p id="_424b7e30-b830-4dc2-93b5-8290586bd041">We suggest that the name “coherent SI units” should be used when it is desired to restrict the meaning to only the base units<index><primary>base unit(s)</primary></index> and the coherent derived units<index><primary>coherent derived units</primary></index>.”</p></quote></clause>
